<br>
I would think that a temporary PvP flag would be in order. That would allow blue characters to buff and heal red characters, but make them vunerable to PvP for a short duration. This would work quite well on the team servers, due to the fact that people still exploit the hard-coded teams.<br>
<br>
For instance, say you see a Dark Elf and a High Elf fighting; If you're neutral, you can pick a side and help, but you'll open yourself to PvP for say, 4 hours play time.<br>
<br>
This system would allow red and blue players to play PvE together, but ensure that blue players aren't invunerable to PvP if they decide to help the red players. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=infotainmentx>Infotainmentx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 727<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/18/03 12:16:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25419.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Blue Server PvP Thought for discussion</span><hr size=1> Thing is, on the normal servers, people are pretty well expecting to never have to deal with PvP unless they specifically want to.  You can't really add PvP-only content at this stage without pissing off a bunch of people.<br>
